====Usage notes====
The comparative is {{m|pl|wolniejszy}} for the "slow" sense, while for the "liberty" sense the comparative is {{m|pl|[[bardziej]] wolny}}. Similarly, the corresponding adverb {{m|pl|wolno}} is typically used for the "slow" sense as a synonym of more unambiguous "powoli", "pomału", while the "freely" sense is expressed as {{m|pl|[[w]] [[sposób]] wolny}}. Adverb "wolno" is however most frequently used in a collocation with a noun in dative ("komu/czemu?") and a verbal infinitive to describe the state of being allowed or permitted to perform an action, in a similar way to passive voice of "to be allowed / permitted". Eg. "Wolno mi rzec" - " I'm allowed to say".

